commitResults.messageBody:
ToModelType create group according to previous group record, which can be modified maliciouly.

To keep it simple and secure, and due to the fact that onw student can only be in one group in current version,
recreate group when adding person is better.

Let's,
* comment out the code to add group
* add student to group (and create group if necessary) when add student to address book.
* auto save the renewed version of addressbook

commitResults.messageBody:
Commands MarkHomework, MarkAttendance leave out the person list inside group without
update.

This can result in ghost student in group but not in AB or mismatch between student in group and in
global AB.

Let's add set student to the group that he/she belongs to.

Refer to this issue
https://github.com/AY2526S1-CS2103T-W11-1/tp/issues/300

commitResults.messageTitle: UG: Advise Mac users to install a specific JDK
commitResults.messageBody:
AB3's use JavaFX is known to cause compatibility issues with most Mac
JDK distributions. In particular, it can cause the UI to show
garbled text due to font issues.

Let's advise Mac users to use a specific JDK that has built-in JavaFX
support and has been verified not to cause the aforementioned
compatibility issues.
